President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Florida due to the effects of Hurricane Idalia. This declaration allows federal funding to be provided to individuals and businesses in the affected areas for temporary housing, home repairs, and other recovery programs. The counties of Citrus, Dixie, Hamilton, Lafayette, Levy, Suwannee, and Taylor are eligible for assistance. Additionally, federal funding is available for debris removal and emergency protective measures. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) will coordinate recovery operations, and more counties may be designated for assistance as damage assessments are completed. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance through the FEMA website or by calling the designated hotline. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.